content: Yes, I am familiar with the Beach Boys song "California Girls." It is a popular song written by Brian Wilson and Mike Love and recorded by the Beach Boys. It was released in 1965 and has since become a classic of surf rock and one of the band's best-known songs. The lyrics of the song describe the beauty and appeal of girls from different parts of California and have contributed to the state's reputation as a place of sun, fun, and beautiful people.
